tags.name: Railroad Park
tags.note: The park features a picnic shelter, restrooms, playground, half-court basketball and wetlands area. The design of this park follows the historic look of the old railroad era and sits adjacent to the Bear Creek Greenway. Dog Friendly

tags.name: Garfield Park
tags.note: Garfield Park is approximately three acres The park offers a playground, basketball court, restrooms, sand-pit volleyball courts, and the City's only "Zero-Depth WaterPlayround." The park is dog Friendly

tags.description: Large, open space and features a community garden and a playground (lawn area perfect for soccer practice and playing Frisbee).
tags.name: Clay Street Park
Scenic Park
tags.note: Scenic Park is 1.5 acres.The park has picnic tables, two playgrounds, a community garden and beautiful views of Ashland and the surrounding hills. View the aerial photo (PDF format). The park is dog Friendly

tags.name: North Mountain Park
tags.note: This park has three soccer fields, two softball fields, two baseball fields, a playground, covered picnic area (the pavilion can be rented for one-time events), and nature center.

tags.name: Hunter Park
tags.note: Hunter Park is approximately 10 acres and is located on Holmes Avenue between Walker and Normal Streets. The park has eight tennis courts, ballfields, a playground, picnic areas, restrooms and the Daniel Meyer Swimming Pool.

tags.name: Sherwood Park
tags.note: It is a small neighborhood park with a playground, bocce ball courts, and picnic area. Perfect for neighborhood parties and get-togethers. It's a very popular place for toddlers.
